race.comment: VASTLY (2) improved last time out with a plugging third over 1600m at Gunnedah. Finds a more suitable contest and can get the job done with the claim. AGE OF AQUARIUS (4) gets out over more ground today on the back of some solid form of late. Most recently finished fourth over 1400m at this track. Ben Looker has registered two minor placings when on board. Sure to run well. HARDYO (1) got the prize two runs ago at Parkes. Couldn't follow that up last time out when twelfth over 2150m at Gunnedah. Finds a suitable assignment and can rediscover winning form. JUST JACKY (3) scored last start at this track to make it two wins from four starts this campaign. Has good early toe so he should be handy in the run. Solid claims on best form.
